I"¿<p>PPAs (Personal Package Archives) are a popular way to install pre-built packages that
for some reason are not (yet) available in Ubuntuâ€™s standard package repositories.
Some common examples that come to my mind:</p>

<ul>
  <li>installing the newest release of Emacs</li>
